497":"1385年–1497年","1361–Female":"1361年–殁","1497":"1497年","1385":"1385年","1361":"1361年","1360":"1360年","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"英国英格兰諾福爾可特易福德","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"英国諾福爾可特易福德","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Pope于1361年出生在英国英格兰諾福爾可特易福德。她和Robert Pope至少有1个儿子。她去世在她的家乡。"},"hr":{"1361–":"1361.–preminula","1360–Male":"1360–preminuo","1385–1497":"1385.–1497","1361–Female":"1361.–preminula","1497":"1497","1385":"1385.","1361":"1361.","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England"},"cs":{"1361–":"1361–Zesnulá","1360–Male":"1360–Zesnulý","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Zesnulá","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, Anglie"},"da":{"1361–":"1361–Afdød","1360–Male":"1360–Afdød","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Afdød","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England"},"nl":{"1361–":"1361–Overleden","1360–Male":"1360–Overleden","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Overleden","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England"},"en":{"1361–":"1361–Deceased","1360–Male":"1360–Deceased","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Deceased","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pope","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>pope</i> (derived via Old English from Late Latin <i>papa</i> ‘bishop, pope’, from Greek <i>pappas</i> ‘father’, in origin a nursery word.) In the early Christian Church, the Latin term was at first used as a title of respect for male clergy of every rank, but in the Western Church it gradually came to be restricted to bishops, and then only to the bishop of Rome; in the Eastern Church it continued to be used of all priests (see   Popov  ,   Papas  ). The nickname would have been used for a vain or pompous man, or for someone who had played the part of the pope in a pageant or play. The surname is also present in Ireland and Scotland.","North German: variant of   Poppe  .","German: translation of   Pabst  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Popov","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Russian Nikolay, Oleg, Grigoriy, Anatoly, Andrei, Arkadi, Dmitriy, Mikhail, Sergey.  Bulgarian or Macedonian Atanas, Dimitar, Yordan.  Serbian Bosko, Bozidar, Branko.","Russian, Bulgarian, Macedonian, Serbian, and Rusyn: patronymic from <i>pop</i> ‘priest’, from Greek <i>pappas</i> ‘father’ (compare English   Pope  ). The name may sometimes derive from a nickname, but celibacy was not enjoined on priests of the Orthodox Church and so the name can indeed mean ‘son of the priest’. In many cases, however, the Russian name means no more than ‘of the priest’ and designates a servant of a priest. Compare   Popoff  , see also   Pop   2,   Popovic  , and   Popovski   1.","Jewish (American): most likely a shortened form of   Popovski   2. Compare   Popoff  ."]},{"name":"Papke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Bernhard, Erwin, Hans, Otto, Willi.","North German (also <b>Päpke</b>): nickname from a diminutive of Low German <i>pape</i>, Dutch <i>paepe</i> ‘pope’. Compare   Pope  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Pope was born in 1361, in Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert Pope. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1361–":"1361–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1361–":"1361–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"1361–":"1361–Décédée","1360–Male":"1360–Décédé","1385–1497":"1385–1497","1361–Female":"1361–Décédée","1497":"1497","1385":"1385","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","Twyford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Twyford, Norfolk, England":"Twyford, Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Pope est née en 1361,